            "id": "e027d496b6754c7382e1f",
            "questionText": "A new high-speed train, with a mass of $!$500,000 \\text{ kg}$!$, accelerates from rest, converting electrical energy into kinetic energy. During this acceleration phase, the train reaches a speed of $!$72 \\text{ km/h}$!$. Simultaneously, its cooling systems dissipate $!$20 \\text{ MJ}$!$ of internal energy as heat due to friction and other inefficiencies. Based on this information, calculate the overall efficiency of the energy transfer from the supplied electrical energy to the useful kinetic energy gained by the train.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "3891d8e1e87b4616b70f5",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by converting the train's speed from $!$km/h$!$ to $!$m/s$!$. Identify the correct conversion method to perform this change.",
